\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces ~(a)~\textbf  {Device cross-section:} Schematics of exposed (top) and hBN-encapsulated (bottom) MoS$_2$ FETs. ~(b)~\textbf  {FET OM:} Fabricated hBN-encapsulated FET.~(c)~\textbf  {Performance of the fabricated devices:} $I_\mathrm  {D(G)}$--$V_\mathrm  {G}$ curves for different drain voltages and key device metrics extracted at $V_\mathrm  {D}$ = 1.5 V.~(d)~\textbf  {Inverter VTC:} Voltage transfer curve of a depletion-load nMOS inverter. $V_\mathrm  {M}$ is defined as the input voltage at which the output equals $V_\mathsf  {DD}/2$.~(e)~\textbf  {Inverter OM:} Fabricated hBN-encapsulated inverter.~(f)~\textbf  {Inverter performance with $V_\mathsf  {DD}$:} Inverter VTC curves for different $V_\mathsf  {DD}$ and the corresponding gain curves.}}{2}{}\protected@file@percent }
